added.title: Crowbar Jones: Origins
added.description: Grizz pitches his Crowbar Jones prequel film to Nom Nom, hoping Nom Nom will agree to appear in the movie.

added.title: Money Man
added.description: The Bears help Chloe present her project for a college science contest. But Chloe's rival makes things difficult.

added.title: Rescue Ranger
added.description: Tabes helps the Bears rescue Charlie after he gets captured by a villainous game hunter.

added.title: El Oso
added.description: In a flashback to long ago, Charlie has an adventure in the Mexican desert.

added.title: Charlie's Halloween Thing 2
added.description: Charlie tells some scary stories featuring the Bears and their friends.

added.title: Escandalosos
added.description: The Baby Bears enter a Mexican wrestling tournament.

added.title: Pizza Band
added.description: The Bears get pizza at Papa Bear's Pizza Cave and wind up replacing the place's animatronic band. They're such a hit that they go on tour!

added.title: Adopted
added.description: The Baby Bears get adopted by an eccentric millionaire and get to live in his mansion.

added.title: Wingmen
added.description: In order to get some sleep, the Bears help an annoying bird find a new mate.

added.title: Braces
added.description: When the Bears go to the dentist, Panda gets braces. But, Panda finds out his braces grant him super abilities and the power goes to his head.

added.title: Christmas Movies
added.description: On Christmas Eve, the Baby Bears defend a video store from getting robbed.

added.title: Imaginary Friend
added.description: The Baby Bears invent an imaginary friend, but the trouble he causes is all too real.

added.title: Tunnels
added.description: The Bears discover a network of tunnels underneath the cave. Are they prepared to discover where they lead to and who dug them?

added.title: Ramen
added.description: The Baby Bears help a struggling ramen chef perfect her ramen and save her shop.

added.title: The Gym
added.description: The Bears go to the gym and get quite the work out.

added.title: Bubble
added.description: Panda becomes a germophobe and decides to live the rest of his life in a bubble.

added.title: Baby Orphan Ninja Bears
added.description: The Baby Bears venture into the sewers and meet a ninja-like martial arts master.

added.title: Fire!
added.description: Grizz's quick thinking prevents a potential wild fire, but the praise he receives from doing so quickly goes to his head.

added.title: Ranger Norm
added.description: When Tabes leaves for a conference, the Bears have to deal with her substitute, Ranger Norm.

added.title: Shmorby
added.description: The Bears get a Shmorby home assistant device and become lazy couch potatoes.

added.title: Snake Babies
added.description: Charlie adopts baby snakes despite the Bears thinking he's not ready for parenthood.

added.title: Sandcastle
added.description: The Baby Bears build a giant sandcastle. But when some kids declare war on the Bears, they must fight to defend their new home.

added.title: Bros in the City
added.description: The Bears star in a reality TV show along with Griff, Tom, and Isaac.

added.title: Lord of the Poppies
added.description: Grizz and the Poppy Rangers go camping on an island, but they soon find themselves deserted.

added.title: The Mummy's Curse
added.description: The Baby Bears must return a mummy to its tomb or else they'll be cursed forever.

added.title: Band of Outsiders
added.description: A gang of streetwise kids takes Baby Ice Bear under their wing.

added.title: Tabes & Charlie
added.description: Tabes and Charlie team up to find Tabes' missing dog, Kirk.

added.title: Panda's Birthday
added.description: For Panda's Birthday, the Bears try to help Panda meet his favorite K-Pop band, Monsta X.

added.title: Sandy Versus the Storm
added.description: When a big storm approaches, Thomas and company must complete all a week's worth of deliveries by the end-of-the-workday whistle, but when Sandy needs repairs, Thomas and the gang will realize just how important Sandy is to the team!
added.originalseriesname: Thomas and Friends: All Engines Go

added.title: Choosing
added.description: Meet Bing and his friends… Join us and celebrate the noisy, joyful, messy reality of preschool life.

added.title: Pocoyo's Puppet Theater
added.description: Pocoyo finds a box full of puppets. Elly helps him build a puppet theater to play with. Now they have puppets and a puppet theater with its curtain, but they are still missing one important thing: the audience!

added.title: Up & Down
added.description: Pocoyo is showing Baby Bird the difference between up and down. To do this, they are playing on the teeter-totter, but Baby Bird is still not quite sure what is up and what is down. They go up to the top of the slide and slide down. But he still has doubts. Finally, they take a ride in the Vamoosh. Baby Bird finally gets it!

added.title: Pocoyo's Breakfast
added.description: It is breakfast time and Elly has made orange juice, milk and cereal for Pocoyo. But Pocoyo would rather see what his friends are having. So he sees that Fred is having seaweed, Baby Bird is having seeds, and his friends the Martians are having meteorites. His breakfast wasn't so bad after all!
